 helped forge a new poetry that re-imagined writing for his and subsequent generations. This first-ever volume of his letters, written between 1945 and 2005, document the life, work, and times of one of our greatest writers, and represent a critical archive of the development of contemporary American poetry, as well as the changing nature of letter-writing and communication in the digital era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPoets, Americany20th centuryvCorrespondence. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aallen ginsburg.  aamerican literature.  aamerican poetry.  aamerican poets.  acelebrated poets.  acharles olson.  acontemporary american poetry.  acorrespondence.  adenise levertov.  aed dorn.  aezra pound.  agreat writers.  ajack kerouac.  aletter collection.  aletter writing.  aliterary artistry.  aliterary letters.  amentees.  amentors.  apoems.  arobert duncan.  astylist.  awriting.1 aBaker, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarris, Kaplan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, Rod, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052024160240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095661240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520956612423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520956612/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY